-- Saudi Water Company Signs $587 Million Jeddah Tower Deal
-- B y   D e e m a   A l m a s h a b i
-- 2013-04-29T12:53:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-29/saudi-water-company-signs-587-million-jeddah-tower-deal.html
Saudi Arabia ’s national water
company agreed to a 2.2 billion-riyal ($587 million) supply deal
with Jeddah Economic Co. for the Kingdom tower project in the
Red Sea port of Jeddah,  Saudi Press Agency  reported.  The state-owned news agency said the 25-year agreement to
supply 156,000 cubic meters of treated and drinking water a day,
enough for 62 Olympic-size pools, was signed by the chief
executive of the Jeddah-based developer, Waleed Batraji, and
Loay al-Musallam, head of National Water Co.  Jeddah Economic Co. is developing the  Kingdom Holding (KINGDOM) 
project, which includes plans to build a 1 kilometer-high (0.62
mile) skyscraper in Jeddah that would surpass the Burj Khalifa
in Dubai as the world’s tallest tower.  Saudi Arabia, the biggest oil producer with the Arab
world’s largest economy, plans to build the biggest desalination
plant in Rabigh on the  Red Sea . National Water plans to spend
$66 billion on water projects over 10 years.  To contact the reporter on this story:
